Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and word learning from text. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses Bayesian models for learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with one-shot learning, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the complexity of learning from a single exposure. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the use of contextual information for learning, which is relevant to computer vision tasks.
